-- Bank of Canada Buys C$800 Million of Securities for One Day
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-01-31T17:20:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-31/bank-of-canada-buys-c-800-million-of-securities-for-one-day-1-.html
The  Bank of Canada  bought C$800
million ($801 million) of securities for one day.  The central bank announced the second round of purchases,
aimed to keep overnight lending rates close to its current
target of 1 percent, on its website today from Ottawa. Earlier,
the bank had said it bought C$400 million of securities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
